rogueMac.description: BSSID (MAC address) of the rogue AP.

rogueApMac.description: Wired (MAC address) of the rogue AP.

category.description: Category assigned to a rogue AP resulting from the application of classification policies.

channel.description: RF channel on which the rogue AP was detected.

band.description: RF band on which the rogue AP was detected.

detectingAps.description: The list of AP detecting the rogue AP.

numberOfDetectingAps.description: The number of APs detecting the rogue AP.

lastUpdTime.description: Timestamp at which the rogue AP was detected.

locatable.description: A parameter indicating whether the rogue device is locatable or not. If the value of locatable is set to true, the rogue device's location can be queried and possibly found (is not guaranteed). If its value is set to false, the rogue device was not locatable on any floorplan.

apMac.description: Mac address of the detecting AP to the a AP.

apSerialNumber.description: Serial number of the detecting AP closest to a rogue AP.

apName.description: Name of the detecting AP closest to a rogue AP.

snr.description: SNR of the rogue AP's transmissions, measured by the detecting AP.

lastUpdTime.description: Timestamp at which the detecting AP was updated.

RogueDetectingApDto.description: The last AP detecting the rogue AP.

cloudPort.description: This parameter, if true, indicates the port is an uplink port used to connect to the cloud.

portId.description: A port identifier comprised of the port's MAC address concatenated with its port identifier. For example, c0-c5-20-aa-33-3f_1-1-1.

vlanIds.description: Comma delimited list of all the VLAN IDs configured on this port.

portSpeed.description: String value indicating the port's speed. The string value contains units, e.g., Gb/sec).

poeUsed.description: The total inline power in mW consumed by the PoE client (i.e., a powered device) connected to the port.

poeTotal.description: The maximum amount of power in mW the port is configured to source to a PoE client (i.e., a powered device).

tx.description: The total number of bytes transmitted by the port since the switch was last rebooted.

rx.description: The total number of bytes received by the port since the switch was last rebooted.

signalIn.description: The utilization of the port's ingress capacity in hundredths of a percent averaged over the most recent five-minute interval.

signalOut.description: The utilization of the port's egress capacity in hundredths of a percent averaged over the most recent five-minute interval.

crcErr.description: The total number of CRC errors detected on frames received by the port since the switch was last rebooted.

inErr.description: The total number of input errors detected on frames received by the port since the switch was last rebooted. Note: an input error includes CRC errors, runt frames, giant frames and overrun errors.

outErr.description: Total number of output errors of any type detected on frames transmitted by the port since the switch was last rebooted.

poeEnabled.description: Parameter indicating whether the port is permitted to source power to an attached PoE client (i.e., a powered device).

usedInFormingStack.description: Parameter, when set to true, indicates the port is used solely for intra-stack communication. A port having this value set to true cannot be used to connect other devices.

portIdentifier.description: The port's identifier. For example, 1/1/10 where the first "1" is the switch's number in the stack, the second "1" is the switch's module number and the "10" is the port number in that module.

unTaggedVlan.description: The untagged VLAN ID of the port.

inDiscard.description: The total number of received frames discarded by the port since the switch was last rebooted.

broadcastIn.description: The total number of broadcast packets received by the port since the switch was last rebooted.

broadcastOut.description: The total number of broadcast packets transmitted by the port since the switch was last rebooted.

multicastIn.description: The total number of multicast packets received by the port since the switch was last rebooted.

multicastOut.description: The total number of multicast packets transmitted by the port since the switch was last rebooted.

portIdentifierFormatted.description: The port identifier expressed as a sortable string value. For example, if the port identifier is "1/1/2", the port identifier formatted is "001/001/012".

neighborName.description: The name of the device connected to this port. The device's name is obtained from LLDP advertisements received by the port.

tags.description: Tags name for the port. The tags name is an administrator configured name for the port, e.g., nickname.

ingressAclName.description: The ACL name for the ingress network interface. Note: this string parameter is non-empty only when the port is associated with an ACL.

egressAclName.description: The ACL name for the egress network interface. Note: this string parameter is non-empty only when the port is associated with an ACL.

vsixIngressAclName.description: The v6 ACL name for the ingress network interface. Note: this string parameter is non-empty only when the port is associated with an v6 ACL.

vsixEgressAclName.description: The v6 ACL name for the egress network interface. Note: this string parameter is non-empty only when the port is associated with an v6 ACL.

lagName.description: LAG name of the port. Note: this string parameter is non-empty only when the port is a member of a LAG.

lagStatus.description: LAG status of the port. Note: this string parameter is non-empty only when the port is a member of a LAG.

syncedSwitchConfig.description: The synchronization status between the switch's local configuration (by an on-site administrator) and the cloud's configuration. When the parameter is false, the local and cloud configurations are not synchronized (i.e., the configurations are different); once automatic synchronization, initiated by the cloud has occurred, this parameter transitions to true.

poeUsage.description: This is for UI sorting. Indicates the percentage of power consumed by the PoE client (i.e., a powered device) connected to the port.

poeUtilization.description: The allocated PoE capacity of this switch in mW. Note: the allocated capacity is the total power currently committed to all the PoE devices connected to this switch.

poeTotal.description: The total PoE capacity of this switch in mW.

poeFree.description: The total unallocated (available) PoE capacity of this switch in mW.

family.description: The ICX family category. For example, if the switch model is "ICX7150-C08P" then the family is "ICX7150".

cloudPort.description: This switch uses this port to connect to the cloud.

powerSupplyGroups.description: The value of this parameter is a JSON-formatted string describing the power group status. The string contains the switch's serial number and an array of objects, one for each active slot in the power group. Each object contains the slot number and fan status.

switchMac.description: The MAC address of the switch's management interface.

crtTime.description: The UTC time in milliseconds at which the device was provisioned (created) into the cloud.

alerts.description: The current number of active alerts (aka alarms) for this switch.

fanGroups.description: The value of this parameter is a JSON-formatted string describing the fan group status. The string contains the switch's serial number and an array of objects, one for each active slot in the fan group. Each object contains the slot number and fan status.

lastUpdTime.description: The UTC time in milliseconds when the switch's information was last updated to the cloud.

staticOrDynamic.description: The IP address of the DNS server used by this switch.

syncedSwitchConfig.description: The synchronization status between the switch's local configuration (by an on-site administrator) and the cloud's configuration. When the parameter is false, the local and cloud configurations are not synchronized (i.e., the configurations are different); once automatic synchronization, initiated by the cloud has occurred, this parameter transitions to true.

provisionName.description: This parameter is the switch's name provisioned by an administrator logged into the cloud. The locally-provisioned name, switchName, will override this value during the synchronization process.

NeverContactedCloud.description: Number of APs being setup and not yet managed by cloud.

Operational.description: Number of APs that are operational and managed by cloud.

Connected.description: Number of APs that are connected but still not transmitting.

Disconnected.description: Number of APs that are disconnected from the cloud.

InSetupPhase.description: Number of APs being setup and not yet managed by cloud. APs in this state for a long time may require technical assistance.

Operational.description: Number of APs that are operational and managed by cloud.

RequiresAttention.description: Number of APs that require technical assistance.

TransientIssue.description: Number of APs that are temporarily offline.

maxPower.description: The AP's maximum power in dBm.

uptime.description: The elapsed time in seconds between the time of the AP's last reboot and now.

lastUpdTime.description: The entity's last modified timestamp in UTC milliseconds.

delegationExpiryDate.description: Delegation expiry date in UTC milliseconds.

txPower.description: The AP's transmitter power setting in dBm.

Rssi.description: A relative indication of the received power level of a client device's wireless transmissions as measured at the AP.  RSSI is scored on a scale of 0 to 100 with 100 indicating a very high (good) received power level and 0 indicating an extremely low (poor) power level.

uptime.description: The elapsed time in seconds between the time of the AP's last reboot and now.

crtTime.description: The UTC time in milliseconds at which the device was provisioned (created) into the cloud.

additionalProperties.description: The total amount of rogue devices for each category.

rogueCategory.description: The total amount of rogue devices for each category.

crtTime.description: The UTC time in milliseconds at which the device was provisioned (created) into the cloud.

additionalProperties.description: The total amount of rogue devices for each category.

rogueCategory.description: The total amount of rogue devices for each category.

additionalProperties.description: The total amount of rogue devices for each category.

rogueCategory.description: The total amount of rogue devices for each category.

guestType.description: It represents guest user type and possible values are GuestPass, SelfSign, HostGuest.

guestStatus.description: Guest status indicates whether the user is allowed to join network or not and the possible values are enabled and disabled.

guestType.description: It represents guest user type and possible values are GuestPass, SelfSign, HostGuest.

passDurationHours.description: The duration of how long this guest user can connect to this network. If the duration value is 7, the unit is day, the duration hours will be 168(7 x 24) hrs.

guestStatus.description: Guest status indicates whether the user is allowed to join network or not and the possible values are enabled and disabled.

delegatedToId.description: Ruckus cloud unique delegated admin ID.

lastUpdTime.description: The entity's last modified timestamp in UTC milliseconds.

authServer.description: The IPv4 address and port of the Cloudpath authentication server in the following format: <IP>:<port>. For example, 192.168.10.10:1812.

acctServer.description: The IPv4 address and port of the Cloudpath accounting server in the following format: <IP>:<port>. For example, 192.168.10.10:1813.
